---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const CDN = "https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/69788340c4a614347d63a918/";
const fmt = "?format=1500w";

const grids = [
  CDN + "8598cb0c-46b7-402b-aeed-34b6bd3a0599/grid1_2026-05-21+a+las+19.22.34.png" + fmt,
  CDN + "f6c6c0ec-b4f9-424c-ab36-09c7f9de06c4/grid+2_2026-05-21+a+las+19.24.38.png" + fmt,
];
---

<Layout title="@by.agnesmercade — Agnès Mercadé">
  <section class="project-detail">
    <h1>@by.agnesmercade</h1>
    <div class="project-description">
      <p>
        A visual diary on Instagram that functions as an exercise in visual curation, art direction,
        and digital identity building, where I share photographs that reflect my personal observations
        and creative process. The account brings together small details, moments of light, textures,
        and everyday scenes that are part of my creative process.
      </p>
      <p>
        This space works as an extension of my photographic practice and as an ongoing exploration
        of the image within a digital environment. Through @by.agnesmercade, I share fragments of
        everyday observations (places, light, architecture, and moments of calm found in daily life).
      </p>
      <p>
        I approach the account both as a personal practice and as a carefully curated visual grid.
        Each image is intentionally crafted so that it works on its own, while also contributing to
        the rhythm, atmosphere, and continuity of the overall feed. The project combines spontaneous
        captures with more thought-out compositions, from urban textures to domestic scenes, exploring
        how light, colour, composition, and subtle details interact visually.
      </p>
      <p>
        More recently, moving image has also become part of the project. Alongside photography, I have
        started experimenting with short video sequences that capture atmosphere, movement, and everyday
        observations. Through these fragments, I explore a different sense of rhythm and presence,
        expanding the way the project translates personal experiences into visual form.
      </p>
      <p>
        Rather than portraying the city as something overwhelming, I am interested in finding moments
        of stillness, softness, and beauty within everyday urban environments. This sensibility is not
        limited to urban settings but extends to all the environments I photograph or film, from natural
        landscapes to more intimate or domestic scenes, with a consistent intention across my work.
        Across both still and moving images, there is a clear purpose: to translate the way I observe
        the world through calmness, subtlety, and atmosphere, and to communicate this way of seeing
        to whoever is watching.
      </p>
      <p>
        Beyond photography itself, the project has become a way of exploring creative direction through
        sequencing, visual storytelling, and the relationship between images within a digital space.
        It is a continuously evolving process, where I examine how images relate to one another through
        aesthetics, coherence, and mood, developing a cohesive visual language over time that feels
        both personal and intuitive.
      </p>
      <p>
        This ongoing practice is an essential part of my work, helping me refine not only a way of
        seeing, but also a growing interest in art direction and image-based storytelling.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="project-gallery cols-1">
      {grids.map(src => (
        <img src={src} alt="" loading="lazy" />
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
